HEADWORD: Strigil
<hw>Strig"il</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>strigilis</ets>, from <ets>stringere</ets> to graze, scrape.]</ety>
<fld>(Gr. & Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>An instrument of metal, ivory, etc.,
used for scraping the skin at the bath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

